Point Cloud Free Viewer is a solution for viewing laser scanned point cloud data inside Unity for free. This repository is meant for people that want to improve the code by making git pull requests.

This is a follow-up from this web page (Retrieved 15th July 2014):
http://www.kamend.com/2014/05/rendering-a-point-cloud-inside-unity/

The code has not been updated since 2014 and it is not mantained. Please follow the updates of other contributors in this repository.

Unity package (version 0.0)
https://assetstore.unity.com/packages/tools/utilities/point-cloud-free-viewer-19811

For a more complete alternative, check out the point cloud viewer from Keijiro Takahaji, as suggested by Albert Callejo:
https://github.com/keijiro/Pcx
